  "answer": "A: F, B: T, C: T, D: F, E: F) The complications of splenectomy include thrombocythaemia which may be treated with aspirin when greater than 1 million. Injury to the stomach during ligation of the short gastric vessels may occur with formation of a gastric fistula. Damage to the tail of the pancreas may produce a pancreatic fistula.",
