  "answer": "A:T, B:F, C:F, D:T, E:F) Renal failure is a frequent event in Intensive Care Units. The commonest cause in surgical patients is hypoperfusion of the kidneys. Acute renal failure presents as oliguria. Other causes of oliguria (blocked urinary catheter, sodium and water retention due to the stress response etc) should be excluded. Immediate management following correction of hypovolaemia includes dopamine infusion, fluid restriction to 20 ml/hr plus the previous hour’s urine output and regular urea, electrolytes and creatinine measurements. Blood gas analysis are essential to identify acid-base derangement.",
