  "answer": "B) Duke’s C carcinoma of the colon has a 5 year survival of 35%. Radiotherapy is used to ‘down stage ‘ the tumour and aid resection. Systemic chemotherapy may be used for the palliation of systemic spread. By definition a carcinoma of the colon is staged Duke’s C when there is evidence of lymph node metastases. A change in bowel habit, weight loss and less frequently macroscopic bleeding per rectum are the commonest modes of presentation of large bowel malignancy.",
