  "markdown_debrief": "### SHARP 4.0 Cognitive & Surgical Debrief\n\n> **💡 Practice medicine with evidence, not just experience!**\n\n---\n\n## S — Set the Stage\nThe correct answer highlights that Evidence-Based Medicine (EBM) fundamentally includes audit and may involve Phase III trials. EBM is a critical framework in modern healthcare, integrating various components to ensure optimal patient care.\n\n## H — Highlight Excellence\nEvidence-Based Medicine is the conscientious, explicit, and judicious use of current best evidence in making decisions about the care of individual patients. Audit is an essential component of EBM, as it involves systematically reviewing clinical care against explicit criteria and implementing changes to improve quality, thereby closing the loop of continuous improvement. Phase III trials are large-scale randomized controlled trials designed to evaluate the efficacy and safety of new interventions against standard treatments or placebo, providing high-level evidence that directly informs EBM guidelines and clinical practice.\n\n## A — Address the Gaps\n\nOption B (Incorrect): Baron Larrey is historically recognized for pioneering battlefield triage, not for initiating Evidence-Based Medicine.\nOption D (Incorrect): Education is a core pillar of Evidence-Based Medicine, alongside research and audit, enabling clinicians to critically appraise and apply evidence effectively.\nOption E (Incorrect): The provided answer key states that cervical screening is not a direct result of evidence-based medicine and has limited evidence of benefit, partly due to selection bias.\n\n## R — Review Learning Points\n\n| Component of EBM | Description |\n|---|---|\n| Best Research Evidence | Systematically reviewed clinical research, often from RCTs |\n| Clinical Expertise | The clinician's accumulated experience, education, and skills |\n| Patient Values & Preferences | The unique preferences, concerns, and expectations of each patient |\n| Audit | Systematic review of care against explicit criteria to improve quality |\n\n## P — Plan (Board Pearl)\nBoard Pearl: EBM is the triad of evidence, expertise, and patient values, with audit as a feedback loop.\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Imaging & Intraoperative Pearl\nWhile not directly an imaging or intraoperative finding, Evidence-Based Medicine principles dictate the appropriate use of diagnostic imaging (e.g., selecting the most accurate and least invasive modality) and guide surgical decision-making, ensuring interventions are supported by robust clinical evidence.\n\n## 📋 Guideline Anchor\nThe GRADE Working Group (2008) provides a transparent framework for developing and presenting summaries of evidence and grading the strength of recommendations in health care.\n\n---\n\n### Answer Breakdown\n| Option | Text | Status |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| A | includes audit | ✅ Correct |\n| B | was started by Baron Larrey | ❌ Incorrect |\n| C | may involve Phase III trials | ✅ Correct |\n| D | does not include education | ❌ Incorrect |\n| E | has led to the cervical cancer screening programme | ❌ Incorrect |\n\n**✅ Answer: A, C) Evidence based medicine is the point of union between education, research and audit. Baron Larrey wa** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Difficulty: Medium** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Source: 57046758-MCQ-MRCS.pdf**\n",
