  "answer": "A:T, B:T, C:T, D:F, E:F) Causes of raised intra-abdominal pressures increase the likelihood of herniae developing. The division of the ilioinguinal nerve following appendicectomy is proposed to increase the incidence of right sided inguinal herniae.",
